      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{honey}}, {{dijon-mustard}}, {{wholegrain-mustard}}, {{garlic}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{black-pepper}} with the {{stock-chicken}} in the slow cooker. Add the {{chicken-thighs-boneless}} and turn to coat. Tuck in the {{thyme-fresh}}. Cook on low for 6 hours, until the chicken is tender and the sauce has reduced to a sticky consistency. Remove the {{thyme-fresh}} sprigs, taste and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Transfer the cooking liquid to a small saucepan and reduce over high heat for 5 minutes until sticky. Pour back over the chicken",
              "cause": "Too much stock, or chicken released a lot of liquid",
              "symptom": "Sauce too thin and watery"
            },
            {
              "fix": "A squeeze of lemon juice and a teaspoon more Dijon mustard balances excessive sweetness. Taste and adjust",
              "cause": "Honey quantity too high for taste",
              "symptom": "Sauce too sweet"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Boneless thighs are forgiving, but 7 hours is the outer limit. Set a timer. If they have dried slightly, add an extra 50 ml stock and stir",
              "cause": "Overcooked past 7 hours",
              "symptom": "Chicken dry"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
